                "description": "<p>This is a post in our <a href=\"http://blog.djangogirls.org/post/137825610883/about-your-django-story\">Your Django Story</a> series where we highlight awesome ladies who work with Django. <a href=\"http://blog.djangogirls.org/post/137825610883/about-your-django-story\">Read more about it here.</a></p>\n \n<figure class=\"tmblr-full\" data-orig-height=\"960\" data-orig-width=\"540\"><img data-orig-height=\"960\" data-orig-width=\"540\" src=\"http://i.imgur.com/QpTlS07.jpg\" alt=\"Image of Emylle Chrystinne, Python developer\"/></figure><p>Emylle Chrystinne da Silva Euzébio is fifteen years old and is a student in her second year in high school. At age eleven, she finished a course as a web designer. More recently, she finished a Professional Programmer course in her city Maceió. She gives thanks to her mother, who introduced her to computing when she was just two years old.</p>\n<p>Emylle Chrystinne is a very curious person who is always looking for new ways to learn. She is proud of her self-taught background, though she regrets that often one needs a degree to be recognized for their accomplishments.</p>\n<p>She was nominated to share her story after organizing <a href=\"https://djangogirls.org/maceio1/\">Django Girls Maceió</a>, in Brazil. Follow her <a href=\"https://twitter.com/PudiMylle\">on Twitter</a>.</p>\n\n<h3>How did your story with code start?</h3>\n<p>Out of ...</p>",
